39:35.275 --> 39:36.862
People come over to the table
and they say,

39:36.896 --> 39:39.517
"Did we see you
on Bourdain's show?"

39:39.551 --> 39:41.068
"Yeah, that was us."

39:41.103 --> 39:42.551
Sometimes we don't
have to pay for the meal.

39:42.586 --> 39:43.827
[laughter]

39:43.862 --> 39:44.896
- There's a million of these

39:44.931 --> 39:46.310
Tony Bourdain stories out there

39:46.344 --> 39:48.379
of just how decent and nice

39:48.413 --> 39:50.827
and accessible
he was to everybody.

39:50.862 --> 39:52.482
- Mmm.

39:52.517 --> 39:55.241
- But the idea that
he could feel self-conscious

39:55.275 --> 39:56.896
or he could feel humbled

39:56.931 --> 40:00.413
or he could feel unable
to form a sentence,

40:00.448 --> 40:03.206
again, I think that's how
most people felt around him.

40:03.241 --> 40:05.862
- And I think that, you know,

40:05.896 --> 40:09.034
Iranians have that experience
of feeling like,

40:09.068 --> 40:12.586
"Hey, this guy
